text: Libyan Civil War may refer to: * Tripolitanian civil war (1793–95), a conflict during the Ottoman period in Libya's history. * 1920 Jabal al-Gharbi civil war (1920), a conflict fought over political offices in the Tripolitanian Republic. * Libyan Crisis (2011–present), the period of conflict in Libya since 2011. ** Libyan Civil War (2011), a conflict that resulted from the Arab Spring and ended with the overthrow of the Gaddaffi regime in Libya. ** Factional violence in Libya (2011–2014), a period of violence in Libya following the overthrow of Gaddaffi. ** Libyan Civil War (2014–present), the current conflict that resulted from the escalation of the previous period of violence and the splitting of the governing bodies of Libya into different factions, after the launch of Operation Dignity and the storming of the parliament building in Tripoli.
title: Libyan Civil War (disambiguation)
